President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New Jersey due to severe storms and flooding that occurred in August 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Cumberland, Gloucester, and Salem are eligible for federal funding for emergency work, facility repair or replacement, and hazard mitigation measures. William L. Vogel has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.